                <head>No. 365.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Bassett</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1873-11-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 1, 1873</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 170.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch No. 251, of the 15th ultimo, has
                    been received. It is gratifying to learn from it that the present administration
                    in Hayti <pb facs="0689" n="593" xml:id="pg_593"/> shows a disposition to
                    provide for claims founded on contract which originated during the
                    administration of Salnave. If such a course should be adopted, it would
                    materially redound to the honor and strengthen the credit of the Haytian
                    government under all future administrations.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
